<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?><?Xpress productLine="ncc-clause" ?><clause xmlns:xt="urn:xpressauthor:trackchanges" id="_2967bf24-9d28-40ac-9a78-751031798c7f" outputclass="ncc-clause" variation="WA"><sptc>9.6.2</sptc><title id="_a77ec7c9-e270-43ec-a9f6-7ca08f269fbf">Roofed outdoor areas</title><archive-num/><subclause id="_03087b48-9c01-490d-8ab9-f9795f73c58b" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_8bdd1748-a1eb-4c4d-a0e9-cb715842f4d3">SubClause</title><num>1</num><p>Unless provided with an <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/1267_2.3.0.xml#_d87c7cc0-d0b0-40ab-9a5b-d070ed6e115e" id="_7c57fddb-0f23-4974-b2fb-2ae43286c804" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">external wall</xref> compliant with <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/1848_1.9.0.xml#_263a5890-898c-4938-a6e8-4bd931480b0f" id="_64eefc1e-2650-4dd4-add0-0b0f36c615a1" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="ncc-clause">9.2.3</xref> a side of the roofed outdoor area must be not less than—</p><ol outputclass="alpha"><li id="_ef11bacd-94ca-456d-bcea-a6b9ffb2283e">900 mm from an <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/9420_0.3.0.xml#_12287a7f-71ac-46bd-a629-7648a4b5a252" id="_5359170e-d6fe-47b3-a4d3-ecc9448c2b72" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">allotment</xref> boundary; or</li><li id="_71144cc7-6508-4aea-8b69-dbf3d7431ce2">900mm from a Class 10 building unless the roofed outdoor area is protected in accordance with <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/1850_1.1.0.xml#_0122a1e6-61f8-40b0-9cd0-506f94854581" id="_4c261dfd-9471-43f1-983d-1dada620ffd5" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="ncc-clause">9.2.5</xref>; or</li><li id="_7b93bf36-48c3-4cd3-bfd5-711d7a34d890">1.8 m from another building or roofed outdoor area on the same <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/9420_0.3.0.xml#_12287a7f-71ac-46bd-a629-7648a4b5a252" id="_b1ca9968-b051-41f0-b84c-1ad032e922bd" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">allotment</xref>, other than—<ol><li>a Class 10a building where the roofed outdoor area is protected in accordance with <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/1851_1.1.0.xml#_5d18cebc-2682-4cbd-b26d-f06c7301c78a" id="_3cb952d5-a69f-4a61-b9d7-9071d4a5cc3b" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="ncc-clause">9.2.6</xref>; or</li><li>a detached part of the same Class 1 building to which the roofed outdoor area is associated; or</li><li>a roofed outdoor area complying with WA Part 9.6 associated with the Class 1 building. </li></ol></li></ol></subclause><subclause id="_b9c01031-f98e-4d7c-be6b-d98220a35754" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_62631938-cce7-4e68-a597-7bd1339466d2">SubClause</title><num>2</num><p>The requirements of WA 9.6.2(1) do not apply to a boundary adjoining a road or other public space.</p></subclause><subclause id="_0ce6ba29-12ab-4014-b28f-867dca8a9644" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_0f2e98ec-0581-4040-922f-d4fe50876d12">SubClause</title><num>3</num><p>Notwithstanding WA 9.6.2(1), a roofed outdoor area is allowed up to but not closer than 500 mm from an <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/9420_0.3.0.xml#_12287a7f-71ac-46bd-a629-7648a4b5a252" id="_009f6e12-9f49-4a86-8222-4cc4b4afc041" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">allotment</xref> boundary or up to but not closer than 1 m from another building, or its vertical projection, on the same <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/9420_0.3.0.xml#_12287a7f-71ac-46bd-a629-7648a4b5a252" id="_156dc621-930f-4606-81ef-c3de80f63b26" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">allotment</xref> when measured in accordance with <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/9340_0.20.0.xml#_05684ba4-a84a-438a-8e7a-018b465aecb8" id="_4b47fa29-8509-4ac9-aaff-f51afeafdf3a" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="ncc-clause">WA 9.6.1</xref> if—</p><ol outputclass="alpha"><li id="_81ab3481-cfe9-4456-92af-7126e8efd294">it has two or more sides open and not less than one third of its perimeter open; and</li><li id="_54b66718-9f8b-4923-8dbe-2ff6f1e36e64">for the purposes of (a), a side is considered to be open if—<ol><li>it is without walls or openings capable of being closed for not less than two thirds of its length; and</li><li>the outermost projection adjacent to that side is not less than 1 m from another building or roofed outdoor area on the same <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/9420_0.3.0.xml#_12287a7f-71ac-46bd-a629-7648a4b5a252" id="_eaf1a218-68e4-44cb-a9ec-1f559f61dd88" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">allotment</xref> or, 500 mm from an <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/9420_0.3.0.xml#_12287a7f-71ac-46bd-a629-7648a4b5a252" id="_0343d1ce-917c-45ca-8655-2f641524f673" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">allotment</xref> boundary or the <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/1267_2.3.0.xml#_d87c7cc0-d0b0-40ab-9a5b-d070ed6e115e" id="_171068e6-c510-43ce-b22b-ef3a31c67f7d" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">external wall</xref> of the building (see <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/10152_0.10.0.xml#_0df1bb3a-7ffa-4413-bbb8-997dcacb41fb" id="_38bc9cf6-6a94-4e2f-a4ef-b96ef5e4fb1a" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="image-reference">WA Figure 9.6.2a</xref>, <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/10155_0.6.0.xml#_42288e27-06b4-40f0-86f3-54e53baa43fa" id="_31361f20-e1f9-43a2-8fd6-919a31609a51" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="image-reference">WA Figure 9.6.2d</xref> and <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/10156_0.7.0.xml#_e6631951-849f-4265-9e0d-b5f58b0ca828" id="_c754900c-54ca-4db3-8f0d-53024b5c0f37" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="image-reference">WA Figure 9.6.2e</xref>); and</li></ol></li><li id="_63b8d0b5-f4a8-4910-9459-6aa3ecba1bc3">the supporting structure of the roofed outdoor area must be constructed from <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/1377_5.9.0.xml#_be8a1d10-4119-4eb0-a014-07a806b104ff" id="_9e0f688c-c4e6-44af-9a92-225e1119af61" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">non-combustible</xref> materials, except that timber roof framing may be used where fully concealed by <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/1377_5.9.0.xml#_be8a1d10-4119-4eb0-a014-07a806b104ff" id="_934f1aaa-8ebe-464a-841b-e1334c59ea6d" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">non-combustible</xref> ceiling and/or eaves lining, roof cover, gutters and fascias (see <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/10153_0.6.0.xml#_e106affa-94dc-4e86-971a-6dcd5000baa2" id="_8fe074a0-2db9-40d7-bcbe-c85255cb9889" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="image-reference">WA Figure 9.6.2b</xref>); and</li><li id="_07eef43f-6c60-4ce1-8cf2-fd1d414292e7">it does not provide direct vertical support to any part of the Class 1 building including but not limited to <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/1267_2.3.0.xml#_d87c7cc0-d0b0-40ab-9a5b-d070ed6e115e" id="_75e7f443-9b1b-4294-9ace-e95df282d6e4" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">external walls</xref>, floors (other than balcony floors) and other internal parts of the building; and</li><li id="_3d45d39c-310a-4530-a245-1542e7684199">it has a polycarbonate or <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/1377_5.9.0.xml#_be8a1d10-4119-4eb0-a014-07a806b104ff" id="_40399e72-0491-4239-98c9-fb392e764540" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">non-combustible</xref> roof covering (see <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/10153_0.6.0.xml#_e106affa-94dc-4e86-971a-6dcd5000baa2" id="_804d7ff2-f34a-40b5-ab21-1c44439217cc" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="image-reference">WA Figure 9.6.2b</xref>); and</li><li id="_adcbe264-b529-405d-9b65-c08e092c2dc0">any ceiling lining and wall cladding, including gables, is <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/1377_5.9.0.xml#_be8a1d10-4119-4eb0-a014-07a806b104ff" id="_19a871c8-3eea-4386-8d51-6e1392b1d1e8" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">non-combustible</xref> (see <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/10153_0.6.0.xml#_e106affa-94dc-4e86-971a-6dcd5000baa2" id="_958aefb2-d61e-4543-8f3f-397a2d06861a" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="image-reference">WA Figure 9.6.2b</xref>); and</li><li id="_559f038b-233f-422d-b54a-aaa0023cf161">the floor for the full extent of the roofed outdoor area, including any framing and supporting members is <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/1377_5.9.0.xml#_be8a1d10-4119-4eb0-a014-07a806b104ff" id="_df5cd0e2-6a19-4bbe-8735-597dbe034481" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">non-combustible</xref> (see <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/10153_0.6.0.xml#_e106affa-94dc-4e86-971a-6dcd5000baa2" id="_f1bbf819-92eb-49ac-98e4-006c7b1529f0" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="image-reference">WA Figure 9.6.2b</xref>); and</li><li id="_8b718cb0-2a56-4f2a-919e-f0d48165f566">in the case where the roofed outdoor area has a common roof structure with the Class 1 building and the roofed outdoor area does not have a ceiling (see <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/10153_0.6.0.xml#_e106affa-94dc-4e86-971a-6dcd5000baa2" id="_63a5cc40-5355-4ca6-8b53-66c7da6a4932" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="image-reference">WA Figure 9.6.2b</xref> and <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/10154_0.6.0.xml#_a5ecfa41-f9f8-46c6-8506-62ad5e3a5c3f" id="_d058a158-4331-4304-b76d-3d2d5c8a35cf" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="image-reference">WA Figure 9.6.2c</xref>), the opening between the top of the wall of the Class 1 building and the underside of the roof covering is infilled with—<ol><li>a <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/1377_5.9.0.xml#_be8a1d10-4119-4eb0-a014-07a806b104ff" id="_1ff49064-0230-4664-b6fd-76d23e184353" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">non-combustible</xref> material; or</li><li>construction clad with <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/1377_5.9.0.xml#_be8a1d10-4119-4eb0-a014-07a806b104ff" id="_dfdb783b-4dcb-473f-aca5-ff3b0d23fd91" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">non-combustible</xref> material on the roofed outdoor area side; and</li></ol></li><li id="_9367e710-7a9d-4e43-b9e4-386f1f81d35e">the roofed outdoor area shall be separated from another building and/or an <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/9420_0.3.0.xml#_12287a7f-71ac-46bd-a629-7648a4b5a252" id="_8cc6f921-b2b3-4557-ae83-c362f373807e" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">allotment</xref> boundary with fences or screens being—<ol><li>solid and constructed from a <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/1377_5.9.0.xml#_be8a1d10-4119-4eb0-a014-07a806b104ff" id="_f8753c66-a1e0-490e-9b75-c330ce4b8668" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">non-combustible</xref> material; and</li><li>not less than 1500 mm in height when measured from the finished surface floor level of the roofed outdoor area and having a clearance no greater than 100 mm between the bottom of fence or screen and the adjacent surface level (see <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/10155_0.6.0.xml#_42288e27-06b4-40f0-86f3-54e53baa43fa" id="_7e4d0d4b-7120-4409-bddd-ab8ada2a959f" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="image-reference">WA Figure 9.6.2d</xref> and <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/10156_0.7.0.xml#_e6631951-849f-4265-9e0d-b5f58b0ca828" id="_f983f9dc-8267-4bbc-b024-3d224a56f2f8" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="image-reference">WA Figure 9.6.2e</xref>); and</li><li>provided for the full length of the side(s) of the roofed outdoor area adjacent to another building and/or an <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/9420_0.3.0.xml#_12287a7f-71ac-46bd-a629-7648a4b5a252" id="_7baa9d07-c4de-43a1-9663-e30e6df5c3e7" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">allotment</xref> boundary (see <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/10157_0.9.0.xml#_19bd844e-e2af-42b2-a41a-df50792f9919" id="_16aa42d9-6fe7-446c-acee-897a5b8a8fed" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="image-reference">WA Figure 9.6.2f</xref>).</li></ol></li></ol></subclause><callout id="_182d35c7-4a1b-4488-a938-284b8d9d41e7"><callout-type ncc-info-type="notes"/><ol outputclass="numbered"><li id="_a7198551-77c0-4225-ba13-5712ad89a828">For the purposes of WA Part 9.6, roofed outdoor areas are verandahs, alfresco dining areas, balconies and the like, and includes such uses when located below another part of the building, such as a ground floor alfresco dining area located below an upper floor verandah or balcony.</li><li id="_a1b06e70-1faf-4eaf-baea-6007183959e8">For the purpose of WA 9.6.2(1)(b) and (c) the roofed outdoor area is considered to be part of the Class 1 building.</li><li id="_b0e9360c-9a00-4c06-8f47-01fa4fe9b73c">For the purpose of WA 9.6.2(3)(i) the wall of an adjoining building complying with 9.2.3 may serve as the fence or screen (See WA Figure 9.6.2f).</li><li id="_08242ac1-0c7a-44db-8117-f3c0e17bf22b">Fences or screens conforming to WA 9.6.2(3)(i) may be constructed from any non-combustible material, common materials include steel or fibre reinforced cement sheeting and masonry.</li></ol></callout><image-reference conref="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/10152_0.10.0.xml" id="_0df1bb3a-7ffa-4413-bbb8-997dcacb41fb" variation="WA"><num/><title id="_31102581-a187-429e-a3c6-0cd4f430df56"/></image-reference><image-reference conref="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/10153_0.6.0.xml" id="_e106affa-94dc-4e86-971a-6dcd5000baa2" variation="WA"><num/><title id="_11ed117c-df94-4eed-9f73-481ac56f3436"/></image-reference><image-reference conref="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/10154_0.6.0.xml" id="_a5ecfa41-f9f8-46c6-8506-62ad5e3a5c3f" variation="WA"><num/><title id="_ff674f71-9fe3-4a2e-ad69-2805904bcb81"/></image-reference><image-reference conref="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/10155_0.6.0.xml" id="_42288e27-06b4-40f0-86f3-54e53baa43fa" variation="WA"><num/><title id="_86867bc0-5704-4674-ab71-9f343a4d9461"/></image-reference><image-reference conref="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/10156_0.7.0.xml" id="_e6631951-849f-4265-9e0d-b5f58b0ca828" variation="WA"><num/><title id="_7eeb29db-76b6-4ee0-9f41-35505a45aca7"/></image-reference><image-reference conref="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/10157_0.9.0.xml" id="_19bd844e-e2af-42b2-a41a-df50792f9919" variation="WA"><num/><title id="_634097db-b298-4146-952e-073ac1d2d229"/></image-reference></clause>